<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>Student Management System</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
  </head>
  <body>
    <h1>Student Management System</h1>
    <p>Welcome to the student management system.</p>
    <p>Click <a href="/campus">here</a> to see all campuses.</p>
    <p>Click <a href="students/new">here</a> to create a new student.</p>
    <ul>
      <% @students.each do |student| %>
        <li><%= student['name'] %>, <%= student['age'] %></li>
      <% end %>
    </ul>
  </body>
</html>

<!-- <%=   %> OR <%   %> is embedded Ruby
The equal sign means that we want to print the output of the expression. Otherwise without it, the code will run in the background, but won't print a result.
